parameters.name: レクイエム・暗い場面

parameters:
\n<Ameria>"Phew... Okay, I've wiped down the child's body, changed the
sheets, and finished cleaning the room..."

\n<Ameria>"...Yeah, that's all the work for today done! Now, let's get
started on studying medical arts--"

\n<Ameria>"--Ah, that's right. I should prepare the meal first. The
priest must be coming back hungry."
\n<Ameria>"What's the matter? Why are you in such a hurry...?"

\n<Villager A>"Oh, Ameria-chan. Where is Luerre-san? Please hurry and call
Luerre-san for me!"
\n<Ameria>"The priest is currently out. I think he'll be back soon..."
\n<Villager A>"What to do... Oh no, oh no...!"
\n<Ameria>"Such a terrible injury! What happened to you?!"

\n<Villager B>"This child went out to play outside the village without
permission! And then, it seems a monster attacked them!"
\n<Village Child>"It hurts... it hurts so much, uwaahhh...!"

\n<Villager A>"Where did Luerre-san go?! The monster's poison is making
the blood not stop! We need to perform medical arts or
else...!"

\n<Ameria>"--It's okay! I can use medical arts! I will heal this
child's injuries...!"

\n<Ameria>"Don't cry. It's going to be okay now. First, let's stop the
bleeding..."
\n<Villager B>"The bleeding stopped! Thank goodness, it's healed!"

\n<Ameria>"No, I've only stopped the bleeding for now! I still need to
close up the wound..."

\n<Villager A>"--It's not closed! Ameria-chan, it's no good, it hasn't
healed!"

\n<Villager A>"It's no use... The wound won't heal...! Is it over, is it
really over, Ameria-chan?!"

\n<Ameria>"It's not over! Until the priest returns, I will keep the
blood stopped!"
\n<Ameria>"It's okay, it's going to be okay! I will... I will...!!"
\n<Villager B>"Luerre-san! This child was attacked by a monster outside!"

\n<Luerre>"Quiet... concentrate, Ameria. Continue to stop the
bleeding. I will close the wound."

\n<Luerre>"...Good, that should do it. Ah, don't move. Stay still just
like that."
\n<Villager A>"...Luerre-san, is this child going to be...?"

\n<Luerre>"Yes, there's no need to worry. But they must rest for a
while. Let me see them again tomorrow morning."

\n<Villager B>"Ah... ah! That's a relief! Truly a relief...! Thank you,
Luerre-san! Thank you!"

\n<Villager A>"I don't know how to thank you enough... If you hadn't been
here, by now..."

\n<Villager A>"That's it, please come to my house tonight! I'll prepare a
feast!"
\n<Village child>"Thank you, Luerre Onee-san. Thank you...!"
\n<Luerre>"Understood. I got it, so don't make too much noise."
